    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The Milwaukee will soon inau-\ngurate a new overland service with\nthe Union Pacific as connection.\nThe equipment will be entirely new\nand of the latest pattern.\n\n\nEdward Dickinson, who recently\nleft the Union Pacific railway to\naccept the position of general. man\nager of the Stillwell properties, has\nsince been made third vice presi-\ndent of the Kansas City, Orient &\nMexico railroad.\n\n\nF. E. Ward, the Great Northern\ngeneral superintendent, who has\nheadquarters at st. Paul, accom-\npanied by Assistant General Super\nintendent H. A. Kennedy, arrived\nin Spokane this morning. Messrs.\nWard and Kennedy are on tour\nof inspection."
    }
